on Haste         +33% Spell Haste           Detrimental ONLY         MIN Cast Time: 3 sec        MIN Dur.: 36 secExtended Affliction      +20% Spell Duration        Detrimental ONLY                                     MIN Dur.: 36 secAffliction Efficiency    -25% Mana Cost             Detrimental ONLY                                     MIN Dur.: 36 sec                    Summoning Haste          +30% Spell Haste           Summon Pet ONLY          Reanimation Haste        +30% Spell Haste           Summon Skeleton Pet ONLY          Summoning Efficiency     -25% Spell Mana Cost       Summon Pet ONLY          Reanimation Efficiency   -25% Spell Mana Cost       Summon Skeleton Pet ONLY          Explaination Summary:Hastes         = Do not effect CH heals                 Do not effect Spells with less than 3sec cast time                 Do not effect Spells that last less than 72 secs                   DD Damage Amps = PB AoEs are not Amplified                 Target AoEs are not Amplified                 DoT Damage is not AmplifiedDoT Damage Amp = DoT does 'x' more tics of damage for whatever last tic did in damage                 Only works on DoTs that last more than 36 seconds (nearly all DoTs)                 Enhancement    = Buffs and Heals (not CH heals)Affliction     = DoTs (not DD or AoE)Pet Summons    = Necros get different summon foci than all other pet classes? /shrug</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br><br><br>Basically Complete Heal(spell), Complete Heal(BP effect), and all other forms of Complete Heal<br>are excluded from Focus Effects, but this was known anyways and is only being included in summary<br>because it is a common exclusion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uilltair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Illtair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF